    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith `--clean`:\n<img width=\"957\" height=\"285\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/732687e0-93ea-4052-b192-b6d1c839ee21\" />\n\nwithout `--clean`:\n<img width=\"957\" height=\"285\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a8996571-9141-4e0d-a7db-d09a877694ec\" />\n\nThe title + repro should be enough to explain. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean --cmd \"lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable({msg = {target = 'msg'}})\"` (try also without `--clean`)\n- type `V:w ! echo 1` and confirm.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo `Press Enter` prompt at least for `target = 'msg'`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2556+gce1154048b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
